Hi,
You forget that people are stupid...I used the unix encryption mechan. in
one of my programs and tried 10 popular names, groups (music and hacker ;) )
elements, etc. and of 500 users I got 15 hits. 
...And it would be so easy to make an unix system quite safe...restict access
to /etc/passwd and force users to use an number and at least one 
upper character in their password - and the brute force method would not
be practical anymore.


